pageContext.claim: “If we hadn't reversed the failed economic policies of the previous administration, the world would not now be witnessing this great economic success.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump became president during an economic boom. The jobless rate was down to 4.7 percent by the time Trump took office, well below the historical norm of 5.6 percent. More jobs were created on average per month in Obama's last three years than Trump's first three years.
